title: Track 29 (1988) Dennis Potter Nicholas Roeg Gary Oldman
description:
"Strange how potent cheap music is".

Dennis Potter is widely acknowledged as one of the greatest screenwriters ever; I have got lots of good Potter from TPB, now I am pleased to give something back. 

Potter's hobbyhorses are in evidence here - his love of popular music, his concern with the meshing of fantasy and reality, his image of a wildly fictional America. 

Also check out pennies from Heaven (1981), it's even better.
